<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian-Israeli Talks Resume in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian-Israeli Talks Resume in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th: Israelis `Wasting Time' </H4>

<F P=102> NC1004144694 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1004144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat's adviser, made a statement to reporters today before 
the negotiations began in Cairo accusing the Israelis of wasting 
time by discussing the details of the withdrawal from Gaza and 
Jericho and the implementation of the limited Palestinian 
autonomy there. 
  He added that by constantly placing impediments before the 
Palestinian negotiators, the Israelis are making it impossible 
to sign the agreement on 13 April, the deadline set by the 
Palestinian- Israeli Declaration of Principles. 

</TEXT>

