<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Presidential Council Delegation Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemeni Presidential Council Delegation Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Requests Help To End Crisis </H4>

<F P=102> NC0804195294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1910 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0804195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 8 Apr (MENA)--Yemeni Presidential Council 
Member Salim Salih Muhammad has said that he requested Syrian 
participation in the military committee or in any political 
activity to resolve Yemen's political crisis. 
  The Yemeni official was speaking to a MENA correspondent in 
Damascus after his meeting with Syrian Vice President 
'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam this evening. 
  He said Syrian officials are now studying the Yemeni 
request. 
  Muhammad described his meeting with the Syrian vice 
president, which was attended by Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq 
al-Shar', as positive. 
  The Yemeni official is visiting Syria as part of an Arab 
tour. 

</TEXT>

