<H3> <TI>   Kakh's Marzel Receives 3-Month Sentence for Rioting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kakh's Marzel Receives 3-Month Sentence for Rioting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104084394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 11 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today the Jerusalem District Court sentenced Barukh 
Marzel to three months in prison, after convicting him of 
rioting near the Prime Minister's Office three years ago. The 
judge determined that Marzel will serve his term immediately 
after he completes his current term in detention. The judge 
pointed out that over the past 14 years, Marzel was convicted 10 
times on similar charges. Ever since he became an adult, this 
person has been violating the law, and his acts indicate that he 
has no regard for the authority of the law and the 
establishments of the state. His criminal record, the judge 
said, calls for severe punishment. 
  Our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that upon coming 
out 
of the courthouse, Marzel claimed that he is being discriminated 
against. 

</TEXT>

