<H3> <TI>   Malek's Efforts Praised </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Malek's Efforts Praised </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104130194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Resignation statement of Prime Minister Redha Malek, read </F>
by presidency spokesman Mihoub Mihoubi] 
  [Text] This morning State President Liamine Zeroual 
appointed Mokhdad Sefi as prime minister, replacing Redha Malek 
who earlier today presented his resignaton and that of his 
government to the state president. The resignation statement 
was read this afternoon before the national press by Mihoub 
Mihoubi, the official spokesman for the presidency. 
  [Begin Mihoubi recording] In the name of God, the merciful, 
the compassionate. This morning President Liamine Zeroual met 
with Redha Malek, who turned in the resignation of his 
government. The president accepted this resignation and took 
the opportunity to praise the efforts made by Redha Malek and 
the government members which he led with all dedication and 
self-denial. Thank you. [end recording] 
  A short while after this the official spokesman for the 
presidency presented a statement on the appointment of Mokhdad 
Sefi as prime minister with a biography of the latter. 
  [Resume Mihoubi recording] In the name of God, the merciful, 
the compassionate. President Liamine Zeroual today received 
Mokhdad Sefi whom he appointed as prime minister in replacement 
of Redha Malek. Mokhdad Sefi was born on 21 April 1940. He is 
married and has four children. He is a former student in the 
Shakyh Larbi Tebessi school and Saint-Augustin secondary school 
in Annaba. He has a degree in physics from Algiers University 
and has made advanced studies in physical chemistry in the 
universities of Algiers and Paris. He obtained a diploma of a 
mechanical and electrical engineer in Paris, and has occupied 
several functions including: engineer of gas works in SONALGAZ, 
the national company for electricity and gas; director of 
industrial projects at the Ministry of Industry; director 
general of coordinaton and control at the Ministry of Trade; 
secretary general of the Ministry of Public Works; secretary 
general of the Ministry of Finance; head of a mission at the 
premiership; head of the prime minister's office; and finally 
minister of equipment. 
  The new prime minister is due to meet the national press 
this 
afternoon, and afterward there will be a handover of functions 
ceremony between former Prime Minister Redha Malek and his 
successor Mokhdad Sefi. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

