<F P=102>   LD1104155494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1500 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi, issued in Algiers </F>
on 11 April] 
  [Text] How can I, as a responsible Algerian who has spent 
all his life at the service of the homeland, run away from this 
responsibility, with the certainty that my country can, with the 
help of God Almighty, get rid of its crisis by mobilizing 
everybody and achieving concord and understanding between all 
its loyal sons, Algeria's sons who love Algeria. 
  Thus I have accepted this heavy and difficult responsibility 
represented by taking in charge the burdens of the prime 
minister while I have in my mind the following basic 
preoccupations: 
  -Consolidating the state's institutions, 
  -Reviving the national economy, 
  -Promoting national solidarity. 
  I hope to find among Algerians--I believe this is 
possible--men and women who have the necessary competence to 
achieve the break up which the head of state called for. This 
is the break up with the negative practices of the past. This 
break up will enable to give to this people again confidence in 
itself and in its government, state, and future. 
  The new government headed by Mokdad Sifi will work for the 
respect of all the commitments which Algeria took at the 
national and international levels. 

</TEXT>

