<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Notes U.S., Israeli Plans To Build Military Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Notes U.S., Israeli Plans To Build Military Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104165094 Cairo AL-SHA'B in Arabic 5 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC1104165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-SHA'B </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mahmud Bakri] </F>
  [Text] Available information has confirmed that the United 
States and Israel are currently planning to set up the most 
sophisticated military base in the Middle East region. A joint 
military committee has been formed to set up the base 23 
kilometers east of the occupied city of Jerusalem. 
  According to information, a senior Zionist official recently 
presented U.S. military officials with two separate maps for 
that purpose. The new base will serve the joint 
American-Israeli interests in the region. It will be equipped 
with the most sophisticated U.S. long-range and medium-range 
missile systems, in addition to multisystem rocket launchers. 
The base will be automatically connected to Sixth Fleet 
operations in the Mediterranean and will act as one of its 
tributaries. American and Israeli military experts will 
supervise the base. 
  Information indicates that the new military base will help 
the Israeli plan of planting nuclear warheads in the holy places. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

