<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Resume in Cairo; Sha'th Makes Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks Resume in Cairo; Sha'th Makes Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1204100494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0925 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1204100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 12 Apr (MENA)--The Palestinian-Israeli 
negotiations relating to the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement resumed in Cairo this morning. The Palestinian side 
was headed by Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political adviser to Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat, and the Israeli side by General Amnon 
Shahaq, Israeli deputy chief of staff. 
  In a statement today ahead of the talks, Dr. Sha'th said 
that 
any agreement that might be reached during today's meetings will 
be announced after the talks. Three committees--the Security 
Committee, the Civilian Affairs Committee, and the Legal Affairs 
Committee--will stem from the Gaza-Jericho meetings. 

</TEXT>

