<DOCNO> FBIS4-12644 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes070yy_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-070 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel, PLO Continue Economic Talks in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel, PLO Continue Economic Talks in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Agricultural Issues Discussed </H4>

<F P=102> TA1104144694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 11 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israel and the PLO have reached an understanding on 
the agricultural section of the economic talks being held in 
Paris. Our correspondent Ya'aqov Balsenboim reports that the 
understanding provides for open borders between Israel and the 
autonomy subject to tight control by Israeli security, customs, 
and veterinary officials. The Palestinians will be allowed to 
export poultry, eggs, and produce to Israel. 
  Industry and Trade Minister Mikha Harish conferred last 
night 
with Abu-al-'Ala' [Ahmad Quray'], the PLO representative to the 
Paris talks, and explained to him the circumstances which led to 
the closure imposed on the territories in the wake of the murder 
in 'Afula and other terror attacks. 

</TEXT>

