<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel, PLO Continue Economic Talks in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel, PLO Continue Economic Talks in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Talks Could End `Next Week' </H4>

<F P=102> TA1104183894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 11 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The heads of the Israeli and Palestinian 
delegations to the economic talks in Paris believe that the 
talks will be wrapped up next week. Avraham Shohat and 
Abu-al-'Ala' [Ahmad Quray'] issued a joint statement saying that 
the talks will not be concluded today, and emphasizing the good 
atmosphere in the deliberations. 
  Our correspondent Gid'on Kouts reports that the imports 
policy and customs duties are the most outstanding problems in 
the talks. 

</TEXT>

