<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Garang's `Secret Visit' to Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Reports Garang's `Secret Visit' to Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1104173394 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1104173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The radio of the Israeli enemy army has reported 
that rebel John Garang paid a secret visit to Israel and met the 
prime minister of the Israeli enemy, Yitzhaq Rabin, and 
discussed with him the possibility of providing assistance to 
the forces of the rebel movement. The Israeli radio said rebel 
Garang had also met Mordechai Gur, the Israeli enemy's minister 
of war [name and title as heard], and heads of security organs 
in Israel. 
  AL-SHARQ of Qatar quotes its correspondent in the occupied 
territories that rebel John Garang ended his four-day secret 
visit to Israel yesterday. There are indications that rebel 
John Garang has in the past made several secret visits to Tel 
Aviv with the aim of getting assistance for his forces. 

</TEXT>

