<H3> <TI>   Ten More Palestinians To Return to Territories </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ten More Palestinians To Return to Territories </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104151094 Paris AFP in English 1428 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1104151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gaza City, Occupied Gaza Strip, April 11 (AFP) -- 
Another 10 Palestinians deported by Israel are set to return to 
the occupied territories next week, a PLO official told AFP on 
Monday [11 April]. 
  "Our delegation in Cairo told me Israel was going to allow 
10 
deportees to come back next week," said Rashid Abu-Shibak. 
  Israel, which has expelled about 1,700 Palestinians since 
1967, allowed 49 Palestinians to return to the territories last 
week. 
  Abu-Shibak was sent back to Gaza by the PLO last week to 
oversee the handover of official buildings as the Israelis 
pull-back. 
  Israeli military officials said they were unaware of any 
decision to allow another group of deportees to return. 

</TEXT>

