<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rao Views Pakistan's Bid To Modernize Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rao Views Pakistan's Bid To Modernize Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1204005494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1204005494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister said acquisition of F-16 fighter 
aircraft by Pakistan will disturb the security environment and 
escalate tension in the region. Addressing the Air Force 
commanders conference in New Delhi today, Mr. P.V. Narasimha Rao 
expressed concern over Pakistan's relentless efforts to 
modernize its armed forces and air power far beyond its 
legitimate requirements. He said that while the cold war has 
ended at the super power level, the security scenario in 
different regions continues to be remain dogged by conflicts and 
disputes. Calling upon the Indian Air Force [IAF] to maintain 
constant vigil, the prime minister emphasized that the IAF has 
to maintain the highest level of operational preparedness. 
  Speaking on the occasion, the minister of state for defense, 
Mr. Mallikarjun, said that India never seeks confrontation and 
her quest for peace should not be misunderstood as weakness. 
Earlier, the chief of air staff, Air Chief Marshal S.K. Kaul, 
reviewed the air power prevailing in the region and its impact 
on the security environment. 

</TEXT>

