<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   One `Pak-Trained Militant' Killed; 7 Arrested in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    One `Pak-Trained Militant' Killed; 7 Arrested in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1204101694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1204101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Kashmir valley, one Pak-trained militant 
belonging to Hezbul Mojahedin was killed and seven others 
arrested in Uri sector by the Army yesterday evening. A defense 
spokesman said an Army patrol party, seeing a trip wire being 
cut, [as heard] immediately cordoned off the area and found that 
some militants were hiding there. The troops asked them to 
surrender, but the militants fired at them. The fire was 
returned, killing one militant. A huge cache of arms and 
ammunition was also recovered. These include three AK rifles, 
three pistols, and 3,800 rounds of ammunition. 
  In Jammu and Kashmir, the police have arrested a militant 
responsible for four incidents of firing and bomb blast in Jammu 
city. The militant identified as Harvinder Singh was employed 
as a constable in the special service bureau. The police have 
also arrested a top criminal, who was responsible for 18 highway 
robberies in Jammu and Udhampur Districts. 

</TEXT>

