<H3> <TI>   Talks To Cover `Entire Spectrum' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks To Cover `Entire Spectrum' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0904091194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in 
English 0800 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0904091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Talks were held between Pakistan and the United 
States in Islamabad this morning to review the entire spectrum 
of bilateral relations. Important issues, including the Kashmir 
dispute, supply of F-16 jet planes and nuclear nonproliferation 
figured prominently at the talks. The American side comprised 
the U.S. deputy secretary of state, Mr. Strobe Talbott, and the 
assistant secretary of state on South Asian affairs, Miss Robin 
Raphel. The Pakistan side included Foreign Secretary Mr. 
Najmuddin Sheikh and senior officials. 
  Later, Mr. Talbott had a meeting with the foreign minister, 
Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali. 

</TEXT>

