<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 11, IRNA -- The Foreign Minstry here 
Monday condemned the savage Serbian attacks on the defenceless 
people of Gorazde as "the explicit breach of the United Nations 
Charter." 
  The ministry in a statement said the indiscriminate 
aggressions of the Serbs against the city, declared as a safe 
haven in the Security Council Resolutions 824 and 836, revealed 
the indifference of the international community towards 
"distortion of human dignity." 
  The statement called on all countries, particularly the 
Muslim nations, to adopt serious and rapid measures against the 
Serbian crimes. 
  Latest reports say that serbian occupiers, encouraged by the 
indifference of the international circles, have intensified the 
massacre and ethnic cleansing operatons in the city in voilation 
of all security council's resolutions. 
  Meanwhile, the Bosnian presidency announced Saturday that 
Serbs had used chemical gases to kill many people in Gorazde. 

