<H3> <TI>   Austrian President, Delegation Pay Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Austrian President, Delegation Pay Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Minister Al-Hasan Meets Delegation </H4>

<F P=102> JN1104202794 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1104202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Talal al-Hasan, minister of state for foreign 
affairs, has received at the Foreign Ministry the delegation 
accompanying his excellency the Austrian President in the 
presence of some officials from concerned ministries. The 
Austrian delegation includes representatives of the Ministries 
of Economy, Transport, and Foreign Affairs, as well as 
representatives of the private, tourism, and energy sectors. 
  During the meeting, al-Hasan clarified Jordan's pivotal role 
in the peace process. He explained the economic difficulties 
Jordan is suffering as a result of the siege on the Port of 
al-'Aqabah and the grave annual losses it suffered despite its 
commitment to implementing resolutions of international 
legitimacy. 
  For their part, members of the Austrian delegation praised 
distinguished relations between the two friendly countries. 
They also expressed their appreciation of the democratic life 
Jordan is enjoying which is represented by entrenching the state 
of law and institutions and respecting human rights. 
  Four joint committees held separate meetings to discuss 
prospects of reinforcing bilateral cooperation in the fields of 
transport, technology, tourism, and energy. 

</TEXT>

