<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Territories To Remain Closed for `Another Week' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Territories To Remain Closed for `Another Week' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meretz Ministers Express `Reservations' </H4>

<F P=102> TA0904144094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 9 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0904144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Several of the Meretz ministers have expressed 
reservations with the idea of imposing a total closure on the 
territories for an indefinite period. Minister Shulamit Aloni 
favors imposing a closure until after Independence Day [15 
April] while granting permits to work inside israel to as many 
laborers from the territories as possible. Aloni told our 
political correspondent Shlomo Raz that the opposition's 
incitement should not dictate the government's moves. 
  Minister Yosi Sarid believes that imposing a closure on the 
territories was necessary; however, Sarid said, the duration and 
scope of the closure would have to be discussed further. 
  Minister Ya'ir Tzaban supports imposing a closure that would 
be limited in its duration and scope. At the same time, Tzaban 
called for vigorous action to reduce the damages the closure 
will cause. 

</TEXT>

