<H3> <TI>   Arabs Try To Stab Policemen in Jerusalem, Hebron </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arabs Try To Stab Policemen in Jerusalem, Hebron </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104144494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 11 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two 15-year-old Arab girls from Wadi al-Jawz tried 
to stab policemen at the Western Wall plaza in Jerusalem, but 
the policemen overcame them. Our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky 
reports that the two apparently managed to enter the plaza armed 
with knives despite the metal detector placed at the entrance. 
  Earlier, a knife-wielding youngster was arrested in East 
Jerusalem as he approached a Border Police unit. Our 
correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that when interrogated the 
youngster he said he sought arrest because of a family feud. 
  A girl bearing a knife was arrested near the Cave of the 
Patriarchs when she tried to stab a border policeman. 
  A large demonstration was staged this afternoon in Hebron to 
protest the ongoing closure of the mosque at the Cave of the 
Patriarchs. The security forces were forced to use tear gas, 
and four demonstrators were injured when they inhaled it. 

</TEXT>

