<H3> <TI>   Hezbollah Supports `Martyrdom-Seeking Operations' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hezbollah Supports `Martyrdom-Seeking Operations' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904175694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0904175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lebanon's Hezbollah has praised the 
martyrdom-seeking operations carried out on Wednesday [6 April] 
by a Palestinian in the town of 'Afula in northern Palestine, 
and expresses its full support for the continuation of such 
operations. 
  Issuing a statement in Beirut today, Lebanon's Hezbollah 
announced: The anti-Zionist struggle is the legitimate right of 
the Palestinian people toward the liberation of the holy lands 
of Palestine from the clutches of the Zionist regime. By 
carrying out their martyrdom-seeking operations, the Mojahedin 
are, in reality, defending the honor and dignity of the Islamic 
ummah. 
  The statement stresses the futility of the path of 
compromise 
with the Zionist regime and states: The people of Palestine will 
never succumb to the bullying of occupiers and compromisers. 

