<H3> <TI>   Fadlallah Criticizes Clinton, Pope </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fadlallah Criticizes Clinton, Pope </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804172394 Tehran IRNA in English 1638 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, April 8, IRNA -- Muslim alim, Allameh Seyyed 
Mohammad Husayn Fadlallah here today lambasted Clinton for 
having called on Yasir 'Arafat to condemn the recent operations 
of the Palestinian strugglers in 'Afula in northern Palestine. 
  Fadlallah who was delivering his sermons at Imam Reza Mosque 
in southern Beirut Friday said no one Zionist is innocent in the 
occupied Palestine since the mere fact of their presence on the 
occupied land is a criminal act. 
  He said the innocent side in the conflict are the Lebanese 
and the Palestinians who are targets of regular attacks of the 
Zionist soldiers. 
  Allameh Fadlallah also criticized the pope for describing 
the 
operations of the Palestinian strugglers as some sort of 
antagonism with non-Arabs, and called on him to support the 
Palestinians that are being killed daily by the Zionists and 
demand the Zionist regime to allow Palestinian refugees on their 
homeland. 
  He said Vatican's recognition of the Zionist regime is in 
fact an endorsement of the occupation of Palestinians lands by 
the Zionist regime. 

</TEXT>

