<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Media Leaders Pledge To Fight Restrictions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Media Leaders Pledge To Fight Restrictions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704140194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1300 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Muhammad al-Ba'labakki, chairman of the Press 
Syndicate, and Milhim Karam, chairman of the Editors Syndicate, 
held an emergency meeting in the Editors Syndicate offices this 
morning. Afterward they issued a statement saying a battle has 
been imposed on the press, which they must fight to the end. 
They added that everything they had been told--assurances given 
to people working in the media and citizens everywhere that 
freedoms were secure--has been proven false. 
  The two media officials said that every Lebanese journalist 
and all those who want to maintain simple freedom of expression 
should mass on a broad front that includes Lebanese, Arab, and 
international organizations and individuals in a confrontation 
that might last for some time but that will inevitably end with 
victory for freedom of expression and the protection of 
democracy and public freedoms. 
  Chairmen al-Ba'labakki and Karam invited members of the 
boards of the two syndicates to a joint meeting to be held at 
1200 on 11 April at the Press Syndicate offices. 

</TEXT>

