<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sidon, Lebanon, April 11 (AFP) -- Palestinian gunmen 
shot dead an official of PLO chief Yasir 'Arafat's Fatah 
movement on Monday [11 April] in southern Lebanon, Palestinian 
sources said. 
  Husayn Abu-Zayd, 47, a deputy to Fatah's former intelligence 
chief in Lebanon Kamal Midhat, was killed with automatic weapons 
in the 'Ayn al-Hulwah Palestinian refugee camp on the eastern 
outskirts of this port city, they said. 
  His killers, two brothers who also belong to Fatah, were 
arrested by Palestinian military police and handed over to the 
Lebanese authorities, they said. 
  An informed Palestinian sources said Abu-Zayd had had a 
financial and personal dispute with the two men. 

