GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Liberation Front [FLN] party is one 
which believes in dialogue and national reconciliation. In 
response to an invitation from Mr. Youcef el-Khatib, adviser at 
the presidency, to attend a meeting on the appointment of 
provisional council members on 20 April, the FLN said that it 
would not attend this meeting because it was not concerned with 
the council's formation. The FLN did not attend the national 
consensus conference and therefore was under no obligation to 
implement the conference's resolutions. 

</TEXT>

