<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Courts Issue Jail, Death Sentences to Armed Groups </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Courts Issue Jail, Death Sentences to Armed Groups </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204133194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Oran special judicial council this morning 
handed down its final verdict in the case of the 10 people 
implicated in the establishment of an armed group. Here is a 
report on the matter from our Oran studio. 
  [Unidentified reporter] The sentences were as follows: 20 
years in jail for one person, 15 years in jail for one person, 
20 years in jail for another person, three years in jail for 
three people, one year in jail for one person, and two people 
acquitted. 
  Last Saturday the Oran special judicial council handed down 
several sentences varying from death to jail sentences against 
an armed group implicated in several assassination operations. 
It also condemned to death in absentia four persons implicated 
in the assassination of a policeman in Telagh, Sidi Bel Abbes 
Province. In another development, the Algiers special judicial 
council yesterday handed down six death sentences against the 
Emir Harik Noureddine group which consists of 13 persons -- five 
of whom are on the run -- while the rest of these defendants 
were sentenced to 10 and 8 years in jail. 
  For its part, the Constantine special judicial court handed 
down sentences varying from death to acquittal sentences in the 
case of two armed groups consisting of 37 people implicated in 
several assassinations, possession of, and trading in firearms. 

</TEXT>

