<H3> <TI>   Tunisia Offers To Mediate for PLO in Peace Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tunisia Offers To Mediate for PLO in Peace Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0404145394 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 4 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 9 </F>

<F P=103> OW0404145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hitoshi Kato on interview with Tunisian Foreign </F>
Minister Habib Ben Yahia by unidentified NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 
correspondent in Tunis; date not given] 
  [Text] Tunis, 3 Apr -- Tunisian Foreign Minister Habib Ben 
Yahia granted an interview to NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN at his office 
in Tunis and commented on the Middle East peace issue. He said: 
"The PLO's headquarters has been located in Tunis since 1982. 
If the PLO so desires, we can serve as a mediator between it 
and other countries." The foreign minister thus indicated that 
if requested, his country, as a moderate party among Arab 
countries, is prepared to actively participate in efforts to 
help establish peace in the region. 

</TEXT>

