<H3> <TI>   Poll Gauges Support for Peace Process, Gaza-Jericho Pullout </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Gauges Support for Peace Process, Gaza-Jericho Pullout </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1004090794 Tel Aviv MA'ARIV in Hebrew 10 Apr 94 p 19 </F>
<F P=103> TA1004090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv MA'ARIV </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Some 39 percent of the public believe the 
government should pursue the political process with the PLO in 
spite of the recent terror attacks, 35.5 percent think the talks 
should be halted, 22.5 percent claim they should not be 
suspended, and 3 percent have no opinion on the matter. 
[sentence as published] 
  These findings emerged in a public opinion poll commissioned 
by MA'ARIV from the Shiluv Institute directed by Yisra'el Olynik. 
  Some 53 percent of the respondents support the evacuation of 
Israeli Army troops from Gaza and Jericho, 34 percent object to 
it, and 13 percent have no opinion on the matter. [passage 
omitted] 
  The poll was conducted among 502 men and women over the age 
of 18, according to a nationwide random representative sample of 
the Jewish population. 

</TEXT>

