<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ramadan Urges France To Play `Prominent Role' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ramadan Urges France To Play `Prominent Role' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1204181194 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1600 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1204181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vice President Taha Yasin Ramadan has received Ahmad 
Shakir, head of the Society for the Promotion of Arab-French 
Ties, and his accompanying delegation. 
  Taha Yasin Ramadan said France should play a prominent and 
positive role in the current stage to help reestablish normal 
ties with Iraq and end the unjust embargo against it. 
  He added that the creative achievements of the Iraqi people 
and the strugglers during the reconstruction drive -- including 
development and strategic projects in all fields accomplished 
with Iraqi capabilities and raw materials -- are the best 
evidence of the Iraq's cohesion and support for the leadership 
of President Saddam Husayn [words indistinct] continue to resist 
aggressive schemes [words indistinct]. 
  Ahmad Shakir paid tribute to the Iraqi people's courageous 
stand under the leadership of struggler President Saddam Husayn 
in confronting the 30-state aggression and its episodes. 
  The meeting was attended by the official in charge of the 
Foreign Relations Bureau of the Iraq Command of the Arab 
Socialist Ba'th Party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

