<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Country Protests Use Saudi, Kuwaiti Airbase Facilities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Country Protests Use Saudi, Kuwaiti Airbase Facilities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1204122194 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1204122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraq has protested to the Arab League that Saudi and 
Kuwaiti rulers continue to make base facilities available for 
American, British, and French aircraft violating the Iraqi 
airspace. A letter from Iraq's permanent delegate to the Arab 
League pointed out the serious threat the violations carry for 
the security, sovereignty, and national unity of Iraq. 
  The American, British, and French aircraft mounted 277 
sorties over Iraq between 1 and 7 April, having taken off from 
bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait. 
  Attached to the letter was a detailed list of the flights 
for 
the attention of the league members. 

</TEXT>

