<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Receives Japanese Ambassador to Tunisia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Receives Japanese Ambassador to Tunisia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204175894 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother president Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] 
received at noon today Mr. Harashima, Japanese ambassador to 
Tunisia. 
  During the meeting, the latest developments concerning the 
peace process, the current negotiations in Cairo regarding the 
implementation of Gaza-Jericho accord, and the implementation of 
the Security Council's Resolution 904 concerning the protection 
of the Palestinian people under occupation were discussed. 
  Brother President Abu-'Ammar also briefed the Japanese 
ambassador on the obstacles created by the Israeli Government 
and its evasion from the commitment to implement the withdrawal 
from Gaza and Jericho at the fixed dates. 

</TEXT>

