<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO, Egypt Said To Sign Security Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO, Egypt Said To Sign Security Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1204164694 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 11 Apr 94 p 19 </F>
<F P=103> TA1204164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Amjad al-'Umari and Zaki Abu-al-Halawah] </F>
  [Text] Cairo -- Informed Egyptian sources have said that a 
security agreement on cooperation and coordination between Egypt 
and the PLO will be signed in Cairo within days. 
  The sources said that Hasan al-Alfi, the Egyptian interior 
minister, and Amin al-Hindi, head of the Palestinian 
intelligence service, will sign an agreement to enhance 
cooperation in security and the exchange of information. 
Moreover, Egypt is to provide training and technical assistance 
to the Palestinian police force that will be transferred to the 
Gaza Strip via Egypt. 
  According to the same sources, al-Hindi presented the draft 
agreement to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat last week for 
approval. 
  Senior Egyptian and Palestinian security officials are 
currently holding joint meetings to discuss security cooperation 
during the coming period. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

