<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Interior Minister Arrives in Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Interior Minister Arrives in Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mentese Told PKK Leaders Not in Country </H4>

<F P=102> TA1204172694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1600 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1204172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, Syria April 12 (AA) -- Interior Minister 
Nahit Mentese said today that the Turkish delegations told 
Syrian officials that the separatist terror organization's PKK 
[Workers Party of Kurdistan] leader Abdullah Ocalan and his 
friends were instructing their organization, from Syrian and 
Lebanese soil. 
  `The Syrian officials deny this, while we insist on it,' 
Mentese said. 
  On the second day of his official visit to Syria, Mentese 
had 
a two-hour meeting with 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam, first assistant 
to the Syrian head of state. 
  In a statement afterward, Mentese said that during their 
meeting with ranking Syrian officials since yesterday, the 
Turkish delegation stressed that Ocalan was living either in 
Syria or Lebanon. 
  `For us, the PKK is the most important problem,' he said. 
'We 
insist on the fact that PKK leaders are based in Syria and 
Lebanon. They claimed that Lebanon was a separate state. Since 
we are aware of Syria's influence in Lebanon, we asked them to 
intervene into the situation. All these talks proceeded in a 
friendly atmosphere.' 
  `They also told us that they condemned the terror actions of 
PKK and it was out of the question for them to cooperate with 
these terrorists,' Mentese said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

