<H3> <TI>   Turkish Interior Minister Arrives in Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Interior Minister Arrives in Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Second Round Talks Held </H4>

<F P=102> JN1304061594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0415 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1304061594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Official talks between the Syrian Arab side headed 
by Interior Minister Dr. Muhammad Harbah and the Turkish side 
headed by Turkish Interior Minister Nahit Mentese were resumed 
at the Ministry of Interior yesterday evening. Members of the 
two delegations, as well as the Turkish ambassador in Damascus 
attended. 
  The two sides continued their discussion of the issues 
tackled during the previous round of talks. They reiterated the 
need to continue dialogue and direct contacts between both sides 
to address all issues that concern both countries. The two 
sides also commended the existing ties of cooperation between 
the two ministries in the areas of security and combating crime. 
They also stressed their eagerness to further promote ties to 
safeguard the two countries' security and stability. 
  Afterward, specialized committees held separate meetings to 
address administrative and security issues of concern to both 
countries. 

</TEXT>

