<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Speaker Meets With Omani Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Speaker Meets With Omani Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1104184794 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1104184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] People's Assembly Speaker 'Abd-al-Qadir Qaddurah 
today received the Omani Consultative Council delegation led by 
Shaykh 'Abdallah Bin-'Ali al-Qatabi. People's Assembly 
Secretary Dr. Ibrahim Za'rur and the Omani ambassador in 
Damascus attended the meeting. 
  At the outset of the meeting, Qaddurah gave a briefing on 
the 
democratic process and the work of the People's Assembly and its 
committees under the economic and political stability in Syria. 
  Shaykh al-Qatabi also spoke about the Consultative Council, 
its work, committees, and tasks. 
  The talks dealt with relations between the two councils, 
relations between the two fraternal peoples, and the role these 
relations and meetings can play in confronting challenges to the 
Arab nation. The talks also dealt with Arab solidarity and the 
peace process. 

