  [Text] Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' today received an 
Omani Consultative Council delegation led by Council Speaker 
Shaykh 'Abdallah Bin-'Ali al-Qatabi. 
  Attending the meeting were Ibrahim Za'rur, deputy head of 
the 
People's Assembly Arab and International Relations Committee, 
and 'Abdallah al-Kharusi, Oman's ambassador in Damascus. 
  The talks dealt with the situation in the region, the latest 
developments in the peace process, and relations between the two 
fraternal countries. 

