<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Briefs Cabinet on Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Briefs Cabinet on Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1204132394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 12 Apr </F>

<F P=103> JN1204132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Ministers met under Prime Minister 
Mahmud al-Zu'bi at 1100 today and reviewed the work of the 
services, economic, and cultural committees. 
  During this meeting, the Council of Ministers also discussed 
current political developments in the Arab and international 
arenas. Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' briefed the council on 
the latest developments and on the results of the contacts and 
visits that have recently taken place. The foreign minister 
stressed Syria's rejection of Israeli attempts to drain the 
peace process of its true essence and to evade commitments to a 
just and comprehensive peace. 
  The Council of Ministers also discussed a draft law on 
endorsing the protocol on scientific and technical cooperation 
in the field of geology between the Egyptian general authority 
of geological survey and mining stores, and the general 
authority for geology and mineral resources in Syria. 
  The Council of Ministers discussed the topics on its agenda 
and the issues submitted to it and made the appropriate 
decisions. 

</TEXT>

