<H3> <TI>   King's Reception of Iraqi Envoy Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King's Reception of Iraqi Envoy Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1204172694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1655 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1204172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman, 12 Apr (INA) -- King Husayn of Jordan this 
afternoon received Hamid Yusuf Hammadi, [Iraqi] minister of 
culture and information and the personal envoy of President 
Saddam Husayn. Hammadi conveyed to King Husayn a personal 
message from President Saddam Husayn that deals with the 
fraternal bilateral relations and the importance of coordinating 
stands with Arab and friendly countries to support Iraq's 
position to have the unjust embargo lifted. 
  King Husayn stressed to President Saddam Husayn's personal 
envoy Jordan's solidarity with Iraq, especially since Iraq has 
proven its compliance with Security Council resolutions, which 
means that the Security Council should now implement Paragraph 
22 of Security Council Resolution 687 and immediately lift the 
Iraq embargo. 
  The meeting was attended by Royal Court Chief al-Sharif Zayd 
Bin-Shakir and the Iraqi ambassador to Jordan. 

</TEXT>

