<H3> <TI>   `Obstacles' To Convening Jordan-Egypt Forum Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Obstacles' To Convening Jordan-Egypt Forum Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1204154094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 12 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM1204154094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Jordanian Information Minister Tells </F>
AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT: No Obstacles to Meetings With Egypt, End of 
April Date Proposed for Committee Meeting"] 
  [Excerpt] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Jordanian 
Information Minister Dr. Jawad al-'Anani yesterday denied the 
existence of any obstacles to the convening of the meetings of 
the joint Jordanian-Egyptian higher committee. 
  He told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that the meetings are expected to 
be held in the "last week of this month," as proposed 
previously. Nothing has happened to change this date. Al-'Anani 
added that it is hoped that the meetings will be held in the 
last week of this month under the two countries' prime ministers. 
  The Jordanian minister denied that there are any problems 
preventing the convening of the meeting. He said that there is 
a joint Jordanian-Egyptian desire to hold the meetings to 
achieve the two countries' interests and work to develop their 
bilateral relations in all spheres. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

