<H3> <TI>   Four Militiamen Hurt in Attack on SLA Patrol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Militiamen Hurt in Attack on SLA Patrol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304113394 Paris AFP in English 1014 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1304113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Marj'uyun, Lebanon, April 13 (AFP)--Four militiamen 
were wounded on Wednesday [13 April] in a bomb attack on a 
patrol in south Lebanon, a spokesman for Israel's proxy South 
Lebanon Army (SLA) said. 
  Two of the SLA militiamen were in a serious condition and 
were flown by helicopter to Israel, the spokesman said. 
  The roadside bomb exploded as the patrol was driving along 
just outside Marj'uyun, the headquarters of the Israeli army and 
SLA militia in south Lebanon. 
  It was the first such attack in four years in that area of 
Israel's self-declared "security zone", a security source said. 
  The SLA militia has been the target of repeated bomb and 
artillery attacks in recent months, claimed by anti-Israeli 
guerrillas, namely the Iranian-backed Hizballah. 
  In March, 12 SLA militiamen were killed and 25 others 
wounded 
in these attacks, the heaviest toll for several years. 

</TEXT>

