<H3> <TI>   Islamic Figure Regrets Delay of Pope's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamic Figure Regrets Delay of Pope's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304061494 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0430 GMT 13 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1304061494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The postponement of the pope's visit to Lebanon was 
the focus of a meeting yesterday between President Ilyas 
al-Hirawi and His Eminence Shaykh Muhammad Mahdi Shams-al-Din, 
chairman of the Higher Islamic Shiite Council. Shaykh 
Shams-al-Din said: We expressed our regret over the 
postponement of the pope's visit, which all Lebanese welcomed 
and prepared for to ensure its success. He said: We have 
already expressed our regret and repeat it now. He added: We 
pray to God almighty that the pope's circumstances will allow 
him to visit. He said: From this forum, the home of all 
Lebanese, from the Presidential Palace, I repeat my wish that 
his holiness will visit Lebanon as soon as possible because the 
Lebanese people strongly desire to see this visit take place. 
Also, the Lebanese Government wants the pope to visit. 
President al- Hirawi has just expressed the same desire and 
urges the pope to visit Lebanon as soon as possible. We hope 
the competent departments in the Vatican will continue to 
prepare for the visit and reconsider the decision postponing the 
visit. He called on those who question Lebanon's unity to stop 
putting this unity to the test, stressing that Lebanon's unity 
is safe and has passed every test. He emphasized that Lebanon 
is too secure for any attempt to fragment and divide it. 

</TEXT>

