<H3> <TI>   YSP Sources Deny Reports of Attack on Aden Governor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Sources Deny Reports of Attack on Aden Governor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1204132494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 12 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1204132494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Congress Confirms, Socialist Party </F>
Denies Attempt on Aden Governor Life"] 
  [Excerpt] Sanaa, London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Sources close 
to Brigadier General Salih Munsir al-Siyayli, governor of Aden, 
yesterday denied recent reports of an attempt on his life during 
which he sustained serious injuries, prompting him to travel 
abroad, where he was admitted to an intensive care unit. 
  Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] sources have said that 
al-Siyayli is carrying out his duties and is available in his 
residence every evening with a number of his advisers in the 
governorate. Informed sources had confirmed the report about 
the injury of the Aden governor, who is the strongest YSP 
opponent to the General People's Congress' policy. 
  AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT contacted al-Siyayli's house, and one of 
his aides said he was in the house holding a meeting with more 
than 30 people. He said that "if he had been subjected to any 
harm, the situation would have been different." 
  Sanaa sources linked these reports with Salih al-Siyayli's 
disappearance and failure to attend the meetings held over the 
past days by Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

