<H4>    Meets Compatriots in Islamabad </H4>

<F P=102> LD1204092994 Tehran IRNA in English 0732 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1204092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad, April 12, IRNA -- The visiting speaker of 
Iran's Majlis (parliament) 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri here Monday 
called for closer ties between the Iranian nation and people of 
other countries especially the Muslims. Addressing a group of 
Iranians residing here, the speaker warned against elements 
attempting to sow discord among Muslims and reminded them of 
their grave responsibility in foiling such conspiracies. 
  Hojjat ol-Eslam Nateq-Nuri touched on the friendly 
Tehran-Islamabad ties and called on the Iranians residing in 
Pakistan to make efforts to further strengthen the ties. 
  The Majlis speaker arrived here Sunday on a five-day 
official 
visit on the first leg of his three-nation tour which will also 
take him to Sri Lanka and Malaysia. 

</TEXT>

