<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Visit of Iranian Parliamentary Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Discusses ECO Common Trade Market </H4>

<F P=102> BK1304030194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1304030194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iranian Parliament Speaker 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri has 
underlined the need for establishment of a common trade market 
of the Economic Cooperation Organization [ECO] member-countries. 
  Speaking at a banquet in his honor hosted by Senate Chairman 
Wasim Sajjad in Islamabad yesterday, he said pooling the 
resources of the ECO member-countries and increasing mutual 
cooperation in all fields are very essential. Nateq-Nuri said 
bilateral fraternal relations have stood every test of time and 
the two countries maintain identical views on several regional 
and international issues. 
  Speaking on the occasion, Senate Chairman Wasim Sajjad 
called 
upon Iran to use its influence to persuade India to fulfill its 
pledge of granting the right of self-determination to the 
Kashmiri people. He said the peaceful settlement of the Kashmir 
problem will pave the way for peace and meaningful cooperation 
among all countries of this region. Sajjad stressed the need 
for regular consultations and cooperation between Iran and 
Pakistan, so that the legitimate rights of the Muslims of 
Kashmir, Palestine, and Bosnia can be protected. 

</TEXT>

