<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Visit of Iranian Parliamentary Speaker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Visit of Iranian Parliamentary Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Visits Lahore, Meets Officials </H4>

<F P=102> LD1304083894 Tehran IRNA in English 0751 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1304083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad, April 13, IRNA -- The visiting Iranian 
Majlis speaker, 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri, arrived in the city of 
Lahore in Punjab Province Wednesday and was warmly welcomed by 
the local Muslim people and ulema. Enthusisastic people 
chanting 'Death to America' and 'Death to Israel' lined up from 
the airport to the city to receive the Iranian Majlis speaker. 
  According to an official at Iranian's culture center in 
Lahore, people from various cities of Punjab had arrived in the 
city and spent the night in religious places as well as at the 
culture center to meet Hojjat ol-Eslam Nateq-Nuri. 
  One of the officials in charge of the welcoming ceremonies 
told IRNA that Lahore was rather spending a holiday today so 
that people could take part in the ceremonies. 
  An Iranian student in Lahore said that such an unprecedented 
welcome by the people had been only given to the leader of the 
Islamic revolution Ayatollah Khamene'i and to President 
Rafsanjani. 
  Upon his arrival to the city, Nateq-Nuri visited the tomb of 
Pakistan's great Muslim poet, Iqbal Lahori, where he laid a 
wreath of flowers. The Majlis speaker arrived in Pakistan 
Sunday and has so far held talks with high-ranking Pakistani 
officials including President Faruq Ahmad Leghari, Prime 
Minister Benazir Bhutto, heads of parliament, Shiite and Sunni 
Muslim ulema, and Afghan leaders. 
  The Iranian delegation will later leave Lahore for Karachi. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

