<H3> <TI>   Paper Views Status of Relations With Pakistan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Views Status of Relations With Pakistan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404105794 Tehran IRNA in English 0939 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1404105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 14, IRNA -- The English daily `KAYHAN 
INTERNATIONAL' here Thursday commented on Iran-Pakistan ties and 
said that all the official and flowery expressions of 'concrete 
fraternal relations' were rich in rhetoric but poor in action. 
The daily wrote in its editorial that though the two leaderships 
thought alike in almost all areas, regional and international, 
they moved with delay when it came to reinforcing their 
economic, social, scientific and cultural ties. 
  The level of economic and cultural exchanges between 
Pakistan 
and Iran in the two years had been far from satisfactory, it 
added. 
  Referring to Majlis Speaker 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri's visit to 
Pakistan and the agreements reached between officials of the two 
countries, the article hoped that the follow-up work would be 
coordinated and implemented professionally as planned and the 
senior officials would not get so pre-occupied with 'priority 
issues' on their return home that they would forget what was 
agreed upon and signed during the visit. 
  The paper concluded by saying that "the existing situation 
is 
disturbing and may damage the excellent political ties Tehran 
and Islamabad enjoy. Our president and the leadership in 
Islamabad should identify and address issues to promote 
relations beneficial to the two Muslim peoples." 

</TEXT>

