<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Arrives in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Arrives in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1404142994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1248 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1404142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, 14 Apr (INA)--The Iraqi parliamentary 
delegation arrived here last night from Strasbourg last night to 
participate in the meetings of the Euro-Arab parliamentary 
dialogue conference due to begin here tomorrow [15 April]. 
  The Iraqi parliamentary delegation, led by 'Abd-al-Karim 
Jihad, member of the Culture and Information Committee at the 
National Assembly, took part in the Arab delegation's meetings 
with the general secretariat of the Euro-Arab parliamentary 
dialogue conference yesterday. 
  'Abd-al-Karim Jihad told an IRAQI NEWS AGENCY correspondent 
in Paris that he made a statement before the Arab delegations in 
which he explained the serious effects of the embargo on Iraqi 
children, women, and the elderly, providing figures, and the 
fatalities and new diseases that infect children and old people 
due to the shortage of medicines. 
  'Abd-al-Karim Jihad, head of the Iraqi parliamentary 
delegation to the meetings of the Euro-Arab parliamentary 
conference, held bilateral meetings with heads of the Sudanese, 
Moroccan, Tunisian, Algerian, Lebanese, Palestinian, and 
Jordanian Parliamentary delegations, who expressed their support 
for the Iraqi people, and stressed the need to lift the blockade 
imposed on them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

