<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Islamic Resistance Blows Up `Important' Roads </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamic Resistance Blows Up `Important' Roads </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304180494 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1304180494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic resistance forces last week carried out 
two brave operations in which they succeeded in blowing up and 
destroying large parts of the road that links the al-Kahla' 
district to the subdistrict of al-Musharrah at various points. 
In addition, they blew up the (al-Ghutayji) bridge across the 
(al-Ghutayji) River, which is a tributary of the al-Musharrah 
River and pours into the al-Qubbah marshland east of the 
al-'Amarah Governorate. 
  He added that the targets were considered two of the most 
important roads of communication used by the regime's forces in 
transporting equipment and troops recently. 
  A source in the Islamic resistance forces clarified that 
resistance groups distributed leaflets in the places where the 
regime's forces were deployed. They warned these forces against 
becoming involved in the regime's bloody schemes. It called on 
them to disobey orders and direct their weapons at tyrant 
Saddam's aides and his collapsing regime, which is on the brink 
of annihilation. 

</TEXT>

