<H3> <TI>   Country To Sign Oil Deals With European Firms in May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Country To Sign Oil Deals With European Firms in May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1304101194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0920 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1304101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 13 Apr (INA)--Oil Minister Dr. Safa' Hadi 
Jawad has said that Iraq is making preparations to sign new oil 
deals with several European firms next month. 
  In a statement to the newspaper AL-JUMHURIYAH published here 
today, Jawad added that the cooperation talks between Iraq and 
European oil corporations have reached an advanced stage, noting 
that preparations are currently under way for signing several 
contracts with these firms after the recent conclusion of 
cooperation agreements with French oil firms. 
  The minister addressed the issue of oil cooperation between 
Iraq and Turkey, saying that the Turkish side has demonstrated 
an urgent desire to reopen the Iraqi oil pipeline across Turkey, 
particularly since the latter is suffering from an unemployment 
that is having political and economic effects. 
  The minister asserted that the oil pipeline that runs across 
Turkish territory is ready for operation once the Iraq sanctions 
are lifted. 

</TEXT>

