<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Emir Issues Decree on Resignation, Government Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Emir Issues Decree on Resignation, Government Reshuffle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304181394 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1714 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1304181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait, 13 Apr -- An Emiri decree issued today 
accepted the resignation of five ministers from the Kuwaiti 
Government formed in October 1992 and ordered a government 
reshuffle. 
  The decree stipulated in its first article the acceptance of 
the resignation of the following ministers: 
  -- Ahmad Muhammad al-'Adsani, minister of electricity, 
water, 
and public works; 
  -- Jam'an Salih al-'Atmi, minister of religious trusts and 
Islamic affairs; 
  - Dr. 'Abdallah Rashid al-Hajiri, minister of commerce and 
industry; 
  - Dr. 'Abd al-Wahhab al-Fawzan, minister of health; 
  - 'Ali Ahmad al-Baghli, petroleum minister. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-12858 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes072_j_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-072 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  13 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304191694 Kuwait KSC Television in Arabic 1800 GMT 13 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KSC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government reshuffle decree: After taking cognizance 
of the Constitution and our decree issued on 16 Rabi' al-Thani 
1413 H, corresponding to 2 October 1992 AD, appointing the heir 
apparent, Sa'd al-'Abdallah al-Salim al-Sabah, as prime 
minister, and decree number 198 of the year 1992 forming the 
government, and decree number 2 of the year 1993 AD appointing a 
minister of state for the cabinet affairs, and decree 150 of the 
year 1993 amending the decree on the government reshuffle. On 
the basis of the recommendation of the prime minister, we have 
decreed the following: 
  Article One: The appointment of Nasir 'Abdallah al-Rawdan 
[second deputy prime minister] is amended in the following way: 
Nasir 'Abdallah al-Rawdan [becomes] second deputy prime minister 
and finance minister. 
  Article Two: 
  -- Ahmad al-Hamud al-Jabir is appointed defense minister. 
  --Ahmad Khalid al-Kulayb, minister of social affairs and 
labor 
  --Jasim Muhammad al-'Awn, minister of communications, 
electricity, and water 
  --Habib Jawhar Hayat is appointed minister of public works, 
  and minister of state for housing affairs. 
  --'Abd al-'Aziz Dakhil al-Dakhil, minister of state for 
cabinet 
  affairs and minister of planning. 
  --Dr 'Abd al-Rahman Salih al-Muhaylan, health minister 
  --Dr 'Abd al-Muhsin Mid'aj al-Mid'aj, oil minister. 
  --'Ali Sabah al-Salim, interior minister. 
  --Dr 'Ali Fahd al-Zumay', minister of religious endowments 
and 
  Islamic affairs. 
  --Hilal Mishari al-Mutayri, minister of commerce and 
industry. 
  Article Three: The prime minister is requested to implement 
this decree and convey it to the national assembly. It is to 
take effect as of the date of its issuance and will be published 
in the official gazette. 
  [Signed] Emir of Kuwait Jabir al-Ahmad al-Sabah; 
  Prime Minister Sa'd al-'Abdallah al-Salim al-Sabah. 
  [Dated] Issued on 2nd Dhi al-Qa'dah 1413 H. corresponding 
to 13 April 1994 AD. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

