<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Meeting With Pakistan Ends; Agreement Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Meeting With Pakistan Ends; Agreement Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1404060294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1404060294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan and the United Arab Emirates [UAE] have 
agreed on a wider basis for close cooperation in joint ventures, 
investment, trade, and the industrial sector. The agreement was 
reached at the sixth session of the Pakistan-UAE Joint 
Ministerial Commission, which ended in Abu Dhabi yesterday. The 
joint commission agreed that steps should be taken to boost 
cooperation in water, power, agriculture, telecommunications, 
education, and narcotics control. Pakistani Foreign Minister 
Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali led the Pakistani delegation at the 
commission meeting, while the Emirian delegation was led by 
Shaykh Hamdan Bin-Zayid Al Nuhayyan, minister of state for 
foreign affairs. 
  The Pakistani foreign minister later had a meeting with 
Emirian President Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan and exchanged 
views on bilateral matters and regional issues of mutual 
interest. The foreign minister briefed the Emirian president on 
the latest situation in occupied Kashmir. 

</TEXT>

