<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Committee Concludes 4-Day Aden Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Committee Concludes 4-Day Aden Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1304185394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1304185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Military Committee today concluded its 10-13 
April meetings in the economic and commercial capital, Aden, led 
by brothers Brigadier General Haytham Qasim Tahir, the defense 
minister, and Brigadier General 'Abd-al-Malik al-Sayyani, the 
chief of the general staff. 
  Over the four days, the committee discussed the best ways to 
implement Council of Ministers' decision number 39 on the basis 
of the accord document concerning the military forces. 
  The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', learned that a 
comrade-in-arms 
spirit, sincere Yemeni brotherhood, and a unionist spirit 
prevailed in the committee's meeting. All felt the importance 
of their meetings and their continuation in order to achieve the 
tasks assigned to the committee, which are based on the accord 
document's implementation, as emphasized by the meeting of the 
Council of Ministers. 
  SABA' learned that the committee will continue its meetings 
in the Ta'izz Governorate early next week to complete what is 
left of these tasks, to work out a plan for military movements, 
and to eliminate any military tensions. The committee will 
present the Defense Ministry's plan to the Council of Ministers 
during its next meeting. 
  The Military Committee meetings were attended by a member of 
the Jordanian military committee, and the U.S. and French 
military attaches. 

</TEXT>

