<H3> <TI>   Minister Dallul Denies Extradition Request for 'Awn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Dallul Denies Extradition Request for 'Awn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304175694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 13 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1304175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Defense Minister Muhsin Dallul has denied that 
there are differences within the government, indicating that 
there are only various views, something that is natural and 
always results in a consensus. He said rumors on this are 
attempts to sow discord and undermine the government. He said 
he expected a Lebanese-Syrian summit soon. 
  Answering questions from Editors Association Doyen Milhim 
Karam, Minister Dallul explained that the investigation into the 
bombing of the Sayyidat al-Najat Church is being handled by the 
judiciary and is continuing. An indictment is expected soon. 
[passage omitted] 
  Regarding the issue of Gen. Michel 'Awn, Dallul said French 
officials have expressed their disappointment with his violation 
of the agreement that was sponsored by France. He added that 
the Lebanese Government has not demanded his extradition because 
Lebanon's problems are much more important than Michel 'Awn. 
Dallul said the amnesty law contains certain conditions to 
which Gen. 'Awn must adhere. If 'Awn continues to violate these 
conditions, the amnesty law will no longer apply to him. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

