<H3> <TI>   Fadlallah on Pope's Postponement of Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fadlallah on Pope's Postponement of Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304180394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 13 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1304180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] 'Allamah Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah has affirmed that 
the postponement of the pope's visit to Lebanon is related to 
divergent policies in the region. These policies are linked 
more to international factors than to internal Lebanese factors. 
He added that if the pope had come to this country, we would 
have welcomed him. We welcome all Lebanon's guests, more so the 
pope because he espouses the issue of coexistence. However, 
since he will not come, he knows better the justifications that 
have prompted him to postpone the visit. 
  Fadlallah said the situation in Lebanon requires it to be an 
oasis of freedom so that the region's problems can be aired in 
Lebanon. Freedom will survive but it might receive some 
scratches, depending on the political conditions outside Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

