<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Majid on Lifting Boycott on al-'Aqabah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Abd-al-Majid on Lifting Boycott on al-'Aqabah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304141594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1325 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1304141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, 13 Apr (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid has revealed the organization's 
readiness to bolster and support Jordan's stance on lifting the 
international boycott on the Port of al-'Aqabah. This boycott 
is threatening the Jordanian economy. However, he added that 
the Arab League has so far not received a request from Jordan on 
this issue. 
  In a statement he made today, 'Abd-al-Majid asked the 
Security Council and the United States to review this stance, 
which is affecting Jordan's economy, to achieve peace and 
stability in the region. 

</TEXT>

