Daily Report 
<DATE1>  13 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Envoy on Problems in Cairo Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Envoy on Problems in Cairo Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304181294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1525 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1304181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 13 Apr (MENA)--Zuhdi al-Qidrah, alternate 
Palestinian ambassador and representative of the Fatah Movement 
in Cairo, has stated that the PLO will not sign a final 
agreement with Israel before an implementable solution regarding 
the geographical jurisdiction is reached. 
  In a statement made today, al-Qidrah said that although an 
agreement was reached during the recent Palestinian-Israeli 
negotiations concerning the establishment of the Palestinian 
police and its number, weapons, and deployment areas, it would 
be difficult to sign a final agreement without resolving certain 
problems. 
  Al-Qidrah expressed the hope that the next round of 
negotiations between the two delegations next week will be 
decisive and achieve the desired positive results. 
  He called on Israel to demonstrate its seriousness and 
credibility by quickly implementing its commitments under the 
Oslo and Cairo agreements, noting that the Palestinian 
delegation is abiding by Palestinian president Yasir 'Arafat's 
instructions to work for the establishment of a just peace to 
ensure the life and future of the peoples in the area. 
  Al-Qidrah affirmed the importance of the Egyptian role under 
the leadership of President Husni Mubarak and Foreign Minister 
'Amr Musa in tackling the causes of any possible collapse in the 
talks from time to time. 
  Al-Qidrah called for reviving bilateral Arab coordination 
among the five Arab parties taking part in the negotiations with 
Israel in accordance with the Arab League Council's decision. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

