<H3> <TI>   Settlers Decide To Conduct Independent Patrols </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Settlers Decide To Conduct Independent Patrols </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1204164494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 12 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1204164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Settlers in the Ma'ale Efrayim local council 
decided, as of today, to begin conducting car patrols and 
lookout posts on vehicles and people traveling on the road from 
Ma'ale Efrayim to the Tapuah junction. Council head Hayim Aviv 
informed the commander of the Central Command and the commander 
of the Judaea and Samaria Division that the decision was made in 
the wake of an increase in hostile activities against Israelis 
on this road. According to Aviv, the settlers are not getting 
appropriate protection from the Israeli Defense Forces. This is 
reported by our settlement affairs correspondent Gil Litman. 

</TEXT>

