<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat's Envoy Visits Damascus `To Ease Tension' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat's Envoy Visits Damascus `To Ease Tension' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1304141494 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 12-13 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1304141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman-AKHIR KHABAR--Instructed by PLO Chairman Yasir 
'Arafat, PLO Executive Committee member Yasir 'Amr left for 
Damascus for talks with Syrian officials following the increase 
in tension between Damascus and the PLO. 
  Sources close to the PLO said 'Amr's mission is to try to 
ease tension and stop the media campaigns Damascus is launching 
against the PLO leadership as a result of the signing of the 
Oslo and Cairo agreements, which Damascus views as deviation 
from unified Arab position in the Arab-Israeli negotiations. 
  The sources said 'Amr will brief Damascus about what is 
going 
on in Cairo, and will discuss the cordon states meeting and the 
possibility for the PLO to participate in it. 
  'Amr was a member of the Syrian Arab Socialist Ba'th Party 
during the 1960's and 1970's, and he was a former member of the 
party's Regional Command. 
  The visit is taking place at a time when the PLO leadership 
is facing a real crisis as a result of Israeli procrastination 
and blackmailing in Cairo talks. 

</TEXT>

