<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Israeli Bus Blast in Hadera </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Reports Israeli Bus Blast in Hadera </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1304191894 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1304191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Occupied Palestine -- The Israeli bus blast in 
Hadera, north of Tel Aviv, this morning has left six Israelis 
dead and injured about 30 others, some seriously. Israeli 
Police Chief Rafi Peled declared that a suicide operation was 
behind the bus blast. The 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam Battalions--the 
military wing of the Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas--claimed 
the operation. It stressed that these operations are to avenge 
the martyrs of the Hebron massacre. The operation also came one 
week after the 'Afula martyrdom operation that left seven 
Israelis dead. 

</TEXT>

