<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th on Negotiations, `Zero Hour' of Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th on Negotiations, `Zero Hour' of Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1504064994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0603 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1504064994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 15 Apr (MENA)--Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political 
adviser to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, has stated that 
there is no substitute for continuing the negotiations with 
Israel and expressed his belief that Israel cannot retreat from 
this path. 
  In an interview with the newspaper AL-AHRAM on 15 April, he 
said: We are now completing the first stage, which will not end 
without entering Gaza and Jericho and without the Israeli 
forces' withdrawal. He added that the negotiating process opens 
the door to the [Israeli] withdrawal, the establishment of a 
national Palestinian authority, the entry of the Palestinian 
armed force from abroad in the form of police, and the entry of 
the Palestinian political leadership. 
  He said: Since engaging in the peace process I have become 
convinced that we will reach this land, that the Israeli 
withdrawal is inevitable, and that there is no going back on the 
process. The process may be delayed and cost lives but there is 
no substitute for continuing the negotiations. 
  Asked about the current phase of the negotiations, he said 
it 
represents the last tussle at the negotiating table. 
  He said: We want to learn the date of the signing of the 
agreement so that we can determine the withdrawal date. We have 
agreed with the Israelis to complete the entry of all the 
Palestinian forces during the first week after the signing and 
that the "zero hour" of the Israeli withdrawal will take place 
the following week. Thus there will be a dual authority for one 
week to avoid a security vacuum. We also supported this. But 
the question is: When will this "zero hour" come? 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

