<DATE1>  13 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Activist Blames Israeli Practices for Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Activist Blames Israeli Practices for Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1304163694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 13 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1304163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] For a local Palestinian reaction to the Hadera 
attack, reporter Mark Weiss spoke with Ghassan al-Khatib from 
the Palestinian People's Party: 
  [Begin al-Khatib recording] Well, first of all I feel that 
this is an expected and unfortunate natural reaction to the kind 
of policies and practices the Israeli settlers and Army has been 
practicing against the Palestinian people almost on daily basis. 
Of course, I feel sorry for the killing of any human being, 
including the persons that were killed in Hadera. But we have 
to go beyond just expressing feelings and see exactly why has 
this been happening and what is the way to overcome it. I think 
that it is happening because of the frustration people are 
feeling as a result of the occupation practices and as a result 
of the lack of progress in the peace process. The only way to 
get out of this circle of blood is simply to advance the peace 
process on a fair basis, and second, that Israel should modify 
its practices and policies in the occupied territories in order 
to reduce the tension and the frustration among the Palestinian 
people. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

