<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Receives European Union Ambassadors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Receives European Union Ambassadors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404183994 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1404183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother president Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] this 
afternoon received the three ambassadors of the the European 
Union -- the troika -- led by the Greek ambassador, Konstandinos 
Theodhorakis. During the meeting, they discussed the situation 
resulting from the arrival of 13 April without the 
implementation of the Declaration of Principles agreement. The 
Israeli withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho that was expected to 
take place was delayed due to Israeli obstructions and 
procrastination. 
  Brother President Abu-'Ammar explained the importance of the 
implementation of Resolution 904 to provide international 
protection for our Palestinian people starting with Hebron. He 
said: We insist on the presence of the European Union within 
international protection, especially since we are dealing with 
it on the economic front as the European Union, in addition to 
the participation of the two peace conference co-sponsors, the 
Scandinavian countries and Egypt. 
  Brother president Abu-'Ammar thanked friendly Greece for the 
financial aid it had presented to the Palestinian police force. 
Furthermore, the ambassadors of the European Union stressed the 
importance of the European Union's presence as a union among the 
international [protection team], and welcomed the participation 
of some of the member-countries of the union as a first step in 
the international presence. The meeting also reviewed matters 
of common concern with the European Union. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
